Linux Server for Pintos Project

Set UP 

1. Linux install - 32bit version

2. gcc-4.4 install  - sudo apt-get install gcc-4.4

3. bochs install
--sudo apt-get install wget
--wget https://sourceforge.net/projects/bochs/files/bochs/2.6.2/bochs-2.6.2.tar.gz/download
--tar xvzf download
--cd ./configure --enable-gdb-stub --with-nogui
--make
--sudo make install

4. Pintos install and Set Up
--cd /home/<pc name>
--wget http://www.stanford.edu/class/cs140/projects/pintos/pintos.tar.gz
--tar xvzf pintos.tar.gz
--vi ~/.bashrc
--last line -> export PATH="$PATH:/home/<user-name>/pintos/src/utils"
--source ~/.bashrc
--cd /home/<pc name>/pintos/src/utils
--make

5. code compile
--cd /home/<pc name>/pintos/src/threads/build
--make check => if pass number is seven, it's a success.

6. excute
-- pintos -q run alarm-mutiple
